  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nWhen sending a transaction with a gasLimit like: `8999999`, a user currently gets an error message: `exceeds block gas Limit`. \r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\nThis error message should instead read `Invalid transaction:  Last 4 digits of tx.gasLimit (8999999) decodes to an L2 gas limit of 99,990,000 - exceeds block gasLimit of 11,000,000. To read up on how to set your tx.gasLimit, see: [LINK]`\r\n\r\nSee: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/1035 for context of how this error message is confusing.",
